# GitHub Management Skill
# Use this skill to interact with GitHub via the `gh` CLI.

## Core Instructions
- **Command Base**: Always use `gh`. If `gh` is not found, attempt to use `/opt/homebrew/bin/gh`.
- **Status Check**: Before starting work, run `gh pr list` or `gh issue list` to sync with the team/repo status.
- **Workflow**: 
  - Create branches using `git checkout -b`.
  - Push and create PRs using `gh pr create --fill`.
  - Check CI/CD status with `gh run list`.

## Common Commands
- List Issues: `gh issue list`
- View Issue: `gh issue view <number>`
- Create PR: `gh pr create --title "Feature: <name>" --body "<description>"`
- Check PR Status: `gh pr status`
- Merge PR: `gh pr merge --squash --delete-branch`

## Auth Note
If you see "not logged in", ask the user to run `gh auth login` in their terminal.
